WEBVTT

00:01.120 --> 00:03.043
NARRATOR: <i>Previously
on</i> Heroes Reborn...

00:03.240 --> 00:05.163
Molly's in here somewhere.
(GUNS COCK)

00:07.160 --> 00:08.241
(CLONES GRUNTS)

00:11.640 --> 00:13.324
DEARING: Well, look
what we got here.

00:13.680 --> 00:15.808
Run, Jose.
Find your uncle!

00:17.920 --> 00:19.160
(EXCLAIMS)
(TASER CLICKING)

00:20.800 --> 00:22.086
TOMMY: Mom, it's okay.

00:22.160 --> 00:23.207
(WHIMPERS)
(SIRENS APPROACHING)

00:23.280 --> 00:24.327
Mom?

00:29.080 --> 00:31.401
Why are we rounding up Evos?

00:32.840 --> 00:34.569
To save our species.

00:35.280 --> 00:36.691
MOLLY: <i>I can't stop Erica,</i>

00:37.120 --> 00:40.329
but I will not help her
kill seven billion people.

00:40.400 --> 00:41.970
(GASPS)
(GUNSHOT)

00:42.960 --> 00:44.962
(ALARM SOUNDING)

00:47.000 --> 00:49.002
(ALARM CONTINUES)

00:53.600 --> 00:55.602
(INDISTINCT CHATTER
OVER WALKIE-TALKIE)

00:59.640 --> 01:02.803
What did Molly mean she wouldn't
help them kill seven billion people?

01:02.880 --> 01:04.041
What the hell was she
talking about?

01:04.440 --> 01:05.521
I don't know.

01:05.600 --> 01:07.045
We got to find out
and there's one person

01:07.120 --> 01:09.088
who has the answers.
Your mother.

01:09.760 --> 01:11.410
You've seen
what she's capable of.

01:11.480 --> 01:12.606
We've got to stop her.

01:14.200 --> 01:15.247
I've got an idea.

01:15.800 --> 01:16.801
This way.

01:17.480 --> 01:18.481
All right.

01:19.320 --> 01:21.322
(TRUCK HORN BLARING)

01:29.040 --> 01:31.202
MALINA: So, why are we
in St. Pierre?

01:31.320 --> 01:32.606
FARAH: Just a stop
along the way.

01:32.680 --> 01:34.444
Along the way to where exactly?

01:34.520 --> 01:35.760
Along your way.

01:35.840 --> 01:38.207
You've seen the signs
as clearly as I have.

01:38.280 --> 01:40.886
I know, my destiny.

01:41.520 --> 01:42.567
I get it.

01:43.360 --> 01:46.091
It's not like I don't know
how important it is...

01:46.160 --> 01:47.571
World-saving.

01:47.640 --> 01:50.211
I just don't know how
I'm supposed to do it.

01:51.240 --> 01:53.527
I mean, I know a lot of
things in theory, but...

01:54.920 --> 01:57.571
When the moment comes,
you will be ready.

01:58.560 --> 01:59.686
I promise.

02:09.880 --> 02:10.926
(WHISPERS) Come.

02:14.000 --> 02:16.685
I need you to stay here.
I have to meet someone.

02:17.040 --> 02:18.451
Yeah, sure.

02:18.520 --> 02:20.727
And be vigilant
about your powers.

02:22.120 --> 02:24.521
No slips. I promise.

02:25.200 --> 02:26.247
Good girl.

02:34.480 --> 02:35.811
ERICA: What
are they doing here?

02:35.880 --> 02:38.406
Some kind of scavenger hunt.

02:39.360 --> 02:41.010
Renautas publishes
the "Evernow" game,

02:41.080 --> 02:42.161
so they're taking
photographs of themselves

02:42.240 --> 02:44.242
at different locations
on the campus.

02:44.760 --> 02:47.081
A Japanese gamer named
Ren Shimosawa set it up.

02:47.160 --> 02:48.400
The girls are dressed as...

02:48.520 --> 02:49.601
Katana Girl.

02:50.640 --> 02:52.768
Hmm. Miko Otomo.

02:53.640 --> 02:55.563
This is a Trojan horse
to get past security.

02:55.840 --> 02:57.205
She's here for the sword.

02:57.880 --> 02:59.609
Get it out of here
and to my house.

03:00.440 --> 03:01.930
I don't need this.

03:03.120 --> 03:05.009
Without EPIC,
we are falling behind.

03:05.120 --> 03:06.804
Although Molly's download
was incomplete,

03:06.880 --> 03:08.882
the EPIC units are still useful.

03:09.120 --> 03:10.485
Our operatives
are using them now,

03:10.560 --> 03:12.050
and they've been distributed
to law enforcement.

03:12.200 --> 03:13.247
Great.

03:14.040 --> 03:16.281
The technology I've spent a year
and billions of dollars developing

03:16.360 --> 03:17.964
is only a partial success.

03:18.040 --> 03:22.125
(SIGHS) We can just arrest
them all for trespassing.

03:22.600 --> 03:24.523
It'll be easy to isolate
them with the EPIC.

03:24.640 --> 03:27.120
No, these are our customers,
and every single one of them

03:27.200 --> 03:28.804
has a cell phone with a camera.

03:29.360 --> 03:31.488
We spoil their fun,
it goes viral in an instant.

03:31.800 --> 03:33.040
You do want the girl, though.

03:33.120 --> 03:34.246
I do.

03:34.800 --> 03:36.131
Send one of you to get them.

03:37.040 --> 03:38.121
Be discreet.

03:38.200 --> 03:40.487
And take care of
Molly Walker's body, please.

03:41.000 --> 03:42.286
HARRIS: I've got the lab.

03:42.840 --> 03:44.683
This one will take the gate.

03:45.040 --> 03:46.166
(CRUNCHES)

03:49.080 --> 03:50.650
(GATE BUZZER SOUNDS)

03:51.200 --> 03:53.202
(INCOHERENT YELLING)

03:54.960 --> 03:56.769
It's okay.
Let 'em through.

03:57.160 --> 03:59.162
(ALL CHEERING)

04:06.200 --> 04:08.328
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

04:13.680 --> 04:16.206
FEMALE ANNOUNCER: (OVER PA)
<i>Remember, registration is the law.</i>

04:16.560 --> 04:18.562
<i>Failure to comply
with registration procedures</i>

04:18.640 --> 04:21.370
<i>will result in severe measures
and penalties.</i>

04:21.680 --> 04:24.729
<i>Help us keep everyone safe.
It's our shared duty.</i>

04:26.840 --> 04:28.842
(WOMAN SPEAKING SPANISH
OVER PA)

04:36.120 --> 04:38.122
Wait.
What is that?

04:38.200 --> 04:40.248
MALE TECH: Tracking device
with satellite uplink.

04:40.320 --> 04:42.687
Eye in the sky, so we
always know where you are.

04:43.000 --> 04:45.731
It used to be the hand,
but we put it here.

04:45.800 --> 04:46.801
(GROANS)

04:46.880 --> 04:48.370
MALE TECH: Wouldn't want
to nick an artery.

04:48.440 --> 04:50.329
You have an allowed radius.

04:50.640 --> 04:52.927
Breach it, an alarm's triggered.

04:54.360 --> 04:56.044
Response time is
less than 10 minutes.

04:56.200 --> 04:57.201
Who responds?

04:57.280 --> 04:58.850
You don't want to find out.

05:00.720 --> 05:02.484
(TIRES SCREECHING)

05:02.560 --> 05:04.562
(ENGINE REVVING)

05:10.200 --> 05:11.964
I think we need
to give her a name.

05:12.080 --> 05:14.128
(SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE)

05:14.960 --> 05:16.610
Jose!

05:25.000 --> 05:31.000
<b><font color="#0E7521">Ripped By mstoll</font></b>

05:44.280 --> 05:45.486
NOAH: What is this?

05:48.320 --> 05:50.288
<i>Brassica oleracea.</i>

05:51.280 --> 05:53.601
<i>Glycine max pasanaca.</i>

05:53.920 --> 05:55.763
<i>Crispum...</i> This is Latin.

05:56.080 --> 05:58.128
It's genus species names.

05:58.200 --> 05:59.804
These are seeds.

05:59.920 --> 06:01.490
NOAH: A seed bank...

06:01.560 --> 06:05.087
A very, very large seed bank...

06:06.320 --> 06:08.527
The kind you build when you're
planning to repopulate.

06:08.960 --> 06:09.961
"Repopulate"?

06:11.840 --> 06:13.569
After an extinction.

06:13.960 --> 06:15.644
Aw, man!

06:15.960 --> 06:17.246
You and Molly were right.

06:19.960 --> 06:21.689
I have no idea
what my mother's up to.

06:21.760 --> 06:23.524
Let's speculate later.
(DOOR BUZZER SOUNDS)

06:23.600 --> 06:24.886
We need to vamoose
before we're jacked

06:24.960 --> 06:26.564
into one of those
crazy-ass pods.

06:26.640 --> 06:27.721
Come on.

06:37.560 --> 06:40.325
MAN: 672, Renkert?
That's it... 672.

06:40.840 --> 06:42.490
(WHISPERS) They're loading
them for transport.

06:42.600 --> 06:43.647
To where?

06:44.480 --> 06:46.528
NOAH: That might be a good
question for your mother, Taylor.

06:47.000 --> 06:49.002
(SIGHS) Evil bitch.
(CHUCKLES)

06:50.880 --> 06:52.370
Evil bitch or not,

06:53.600 --> 06:55.489
you're about
to mend fences with her.

07:40.480 --> 07:42.005
Joanne?

07:44.120 --> 07:45.201
Hello?

08:19.760 --> 08:21.091
(SIGHS)

08:21.760 --> 08:23.762
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

08:24.880 --> 08:25.961
(ENGINE STARTS)

08:36.440 --> 08:37.486
(SIGHS)

08:39.080 --> 08:41.082
(CELL PHONE DIALING)

08:42.840 --> 08:44.808
Caspar, it's Farah, again.

08:44.920 --> 08:47.161
We've been here for hours.
Our contact hasn't shown up.

08:47.240 --> 08:48.321
Call me.

08:48.400 --> 08:49.686
(CELL PHONE BEEPS)

08:59.880 --> 09:00.881
(EVO MARKER BEEPS)

09:00.960 --> 09:02.450
(POWERING UP)

09:02.680 --> 09:04.842
(PROCESSING)

09:10.920 --> 09:12.331
She's headed east.

09:15.240 --> 09:17.288
(CHATTERING)

09:17.800 --> 09:19.802
(EVO MARKER BEEPS,
POWERING UP)

09:28.800 --> 09:30.882
(CONVERSING IN JAPANESE)

10:46.920 --> 10:48.001
(CLICK)

10:48.080 --> 10:50.651
DENNIS: (RECORDED VOICE) <i>You're the
best daddy in the whole world.</i>

10:51.240 --> 10:52.651
<i>I love you, Daddy.</i>

10:59.920 --> 11:02.366
FEMALE ANNOUNCER: (OVER PA)
<i>Remember, registration is the law.</i>

11:03.480 --> 11:05.164
So what are you
running from, Tommy?

11:05.560 --> 11:06.686
(CHEWING)

11:07.400 --> 11:08.731
Should I call you Kevin?

11:09.560 --> 11:11.562
Or Michael? Or Justin?

11:13.000 --> 11:14.161
Five aliases,

11:14.760 --> 11:17.161
that's got to be a record

11:17.760 --> 11:18.921
for someone your age.

11:19.600 --> 11:21.329
So, I'm gonna ask you again.

11:23.800 --> 11:26.929
What are you and your
mother running from?

11:27.960 --> 11:30.327
You and people like you.

11:30.400 --> 11:32.004
People like me need laws

11:32.280 --> 11:34.044
to protect us

11:35.120 --> 11:37.168
from people like you.

11:37.960 --> 11:39.689
That's what the Odessa
Protocol's all about.

11:40.120 --> 11:41.531
Wait. ls that what's
gonna happen to me?

11:41.600 --> 11:42.726
Am I gonna disappear
like the other...

11:42.800 --> 11:43.961
What about my mom?

11:44.040 --> 11:45.166
I don't know what's gonna happen

11:45.240 --> 11:46.366
until we get
a few things cleared,

11:46.440 --> 11:49.569
so why don't we start with you
telling me your real name?

11:54.640 --> 11:55.971
(SIGHS) It's Tommy.

11:58.600 --> 11:59.806
The others were fake.

12:00.480 --> 12:01.641
Your last name?

12:02.520 --> 12:04.488
- Clark.
AGENT CUTLER: Your real last name.

12:05.360 --> 12:06.964
The one you had
before you were adopted.

12:13.240 --> 12:16.130
Unless you were adopted
when you were an infant

12:16.200 --> 12:17.531
and you don't remember.

12:17.600 --> 12:20.251
- No, I'm not adopted.
AGENT CUTLER: Your blood type is AB,

12:20.320 --> 12:22.004
your mother's is O-negative,

12:22.560 --> 12:24.210
so, biologically speaking,

12:24.280 --> 12:26.009
- there's no way that could happen...
- What about my father?

12:26.080 --> 12:28.686
No matter what blood type
your father had.

12:31.840 --> 12:33.842
Anne Clark isn't
your birth mother.

12:40.720 --> 12:42.882
So we need to find
your birth parents,

12:42.960 --> 12:45.008
in case they're
unregistered as well.

12:46.240 --> 12:48.242
Meantime, I am logging
your abilities

12:48.320 --> 12:49.924
and your tracking number.

12:50.000 --> 12:53.561
You're required to report any
changes in your teleportation power

12:53.640 --> 12:55.768
or if you develop
any new abilities.

13:01.200 --> 13:02.690
(CELL PHONE DIALING)

13:05.320 --> 13:06.526
He's gone. (SIGHS)

13:07.280 --> 13:08.770
Lock down the hospital.

13:09.320 --> 13:10.367
(CELL PHONE BEEPS)

13:16.000 --> 13:18.401
Penny for your thoughts,
Agent Cutler.

13:24.720 --> 13:26.290
(FOOTSTEPS)

13:28.560 --> 13:30.528
(FARAH PANTING)

13:31.160 --> 13:32.525
What is it?
What's wrong?

13:32.600 --> 13:33.806
We were supposed
to meet someone,

13:34.400 --> 13:36.164
and I'm pretty sure
I had a tail.

13:37.440 --> 13:38.930
I think you still do.

13:42.520 --> 13:44.488
What's happening?
Who are they?

13:49.120 --> 13:50.201
HARRIS CLONE: Where is it?

13:50.280 --> 13:51.441
Where's the baby?

13:54.880 --> 13:55.961
(EVO MARKER PROCESSING)

14:01.600 --> 14:03.921
I'm afraid your powers
can't hide you anymore.

14:05.000 --> 14:06.684
The next one won't miss.

14:08.280 --> 14:09.361
Farah!

14:10.760 --> 14:12.125
(GUNSHOT)
(GROANS)

14:12.440 --> 14:13.771
(GRUNTS)
(WIND WHOOSHING)

14:14.320 --> 14:15.481
(BOTH GROANING)

14:21.440 --> 14:22.851
Malina, <i>chalo</i>.

14:25.000 --> 14:26.047
<i>Chalo!</i>

14:28.080 --> 14:30.082
(SIREN WAILING)

14:33.680 --> 14:35.205
I want to see Detective Dearing.

14:35.280 --> 14:36.645
Something he's investigating?

14:36.720 --> 14:38.006
No, something he committed.

14:38.960 --> 14:41.645
My nephew Jose,
he's 12 years old

14:41.800 --> 14:43.723
and Father Mauricio
from Saint Francis,

14:43.800 --> 14:45.165
they're both missing.

14:45.280 --> 14:47.123
And they were
at my family's auto shop.

14:50.280 --> 14:51.645
Dearing knows where they are.

14:52.040 --> 14:54.646
Kidnapping's
a pretty serious charge.

14:54.720 --> 14:56.768
Yes, it is. So, like I said,
if I could talk to him...

14:56.840 --> 14:58.330
Wait right here.

15:03.320 --> 15:05.971
Guy out front here says you might
know something about a kidnapping.

15:06.040 --> 15:08.805
A couple people disappeared from
an auto shop on Las Flores.

15:08.880 --> 15:10.041
Really?

15:13.840 --> 15:15.365
Doesn't ring a bell.

15:16.120 --> 15:18.361
Have him take a seat.
I'll be there in a minute.

15:22.840 --> 15:24.808
Hey, Dearing, check this out.

15:25.680 --> 15:27.489
These new EPIC things
finally showed up.

15:30.840 --> 15:33.525
Do you really think these things can
tell you if there's an Evo in the room?

15:33.600 --> 15:35.602
(EVO MARKER BEEPS,
POWERING UP)

15:38.760 --> 15:40.046
Where you going, boss?

15:40.120 --> 15:42.168
(EVO MARKER BEEPS,
POWERING UP)

15:43.400 --> 15:45.209
I left my phone in the car.
(EVO MARKER PROCESSING)

15:50.400 --> 15:51.481
(BOTH GRUNT)

15:51.640 --> 15:52.766
(GROANS)
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.

15:57.880 --> 15:59.450
Back off.
We'll handle this.

15:59.720 --> 16:01.290
- Get back to work.
(GRUNTING)

16:01.720 --> 16:03.210
You should have told us, man.

16:03.960 --> 16:05.610
You know what we have
to do to you now.

16:06.960 --> 16:07.961
Let's get him up.
Get up.

16:08.040 --> 16:09.485
(GRUNTING)

16:34.280 --> 16:35.441
(DEVICE BEEPING)

16:39.080 --> 16:41.082
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

16:52.040 --> 16:53.166
(DEVICE BEEPS)

17:05.520 --> 17:06.806
Let's get ready.

17:13.119 --> 17:14.201
Erica.

17:14.720 --> 17:16.131
Great. We're almost
ready for you.

17:16.319 --> 17:17.526
Thank you, Richard.

17:17.960 --> 17:19.883
- Everything okay?
- Fine, yes.

17:21.000 --> 17:22.365
Family stuff.

17:23.160 --> 17:24.491
You have a daughter, don't you?

17:24.960 --> 17:28.042
I do, but she's six,
so she thinks I'm a god.

17:28.119 --> 17:29.201
(CHUCKLES)

17:29.440 --> 17:30.487
Maybe she's right.

17:31.680 --> 17:33.887
What you're doing is godlike.

17:34.120 --> 17:37.567
The next Big Bang
without the noise or the mess.

17:37.880 --> 17:38.961
You ready?

17:40.720 --> 17:41.767
All clear.

17:42.360 --> 17:44.283
(MACHINE BUZZING)

17:44.360 --> 17:46.408
(MACHINE POWERING UP)

17:53.960 --> 17:55.530
- Phenomenal.
- Hmm.

17:55.600 --> 17:57.762
It is just phenomenal, Richard.

17:58.560 --> 18:02.406
We've built an entire company based on
mining the power of Evos, but this...

18:03.800 --> 18:06.531
This one's power is
by far the most important.

18:07.320 --> 18:09.402
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

18:10.000 --> 18:11.445
Excuse me.

18:11.520 --> 18:12.521
(CELL PHONE BEEPS)

18:16.320 --> 18:18.926
TAYLOR: (ON PHONE)
(SOBBING) <i>Mom. I'm sorry.</i>

18:19.360 --> 18:21.124
I didn't mean for it
to go that far.

18:21.200 --> 18:23.328
I was just trying to get back
at you because of Francis.

18:23.400 --> 18:24.970
I know it was childish of me.

18:25.240 --> 18:26.526
Yes, it was.

18:26.600 --> 18:27.647
TAYLOR: <i>Can we talk?</i>

18:27.880 --> 18:29.769
Please? Face-to-face?

18:31.960 --> 18:33.530
Where are you, Taylor?

18:33.800 --> 18:35.370
TAYLOR: <i>At the house.</i>

18:36.520 --> 18:38.010
<i>I just really need to talk.</i>

18:38.920 --> 18:40.001
I'll meet you there.

18:41.440 --> 18:42.521
(SNIFFLES)
(PHONE BEEPS)

18:42.760 --> 18:45.161
I've always been
an excellent fake crier.

18:46.280 --> 18:47.486
(SIGHS)

18:47.560 --> 18:49.210
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

18:51.160 --> 18:52.525
(EVO MARKER BEEPS,
POWERING UP)

18:54.720 --> 18:56.165
(EVO MARKER PROCESSING)

18:59.400 --> 19:00.890
(PROCESSING CONTINUES)

19:04.720 --> 19:05.846
(PANTING)

19:08.800 --> 19:10.848
(CONVERSING IN JAPANESE)

19:19.560 --> 19:21.085
(PANTING)

19:29.240 --> 19:30.401
Hey, what the hell?

19:30.520 --> 19:31.567
We paid our rent.

19:31.800 --> 19:33.290
I don't rent to Evos.

19:33.400 --> 19:34.811
You can't just throw us out.

19:34.880 --> 19:37.281
You didn't register, and
that's grounds for eviction.

19:39.040 --> 19:40.769
You've got 30 days to comply.

19:53.440 --> 19:54.680
I don't see them.

19:55.120 --> 19:56.485
Them who?

19:58.680 --> 20:00.603
- Who were those people?
- Renautas.

20:01.760 --> 20:02.921
MALINA: Who's that?

20:03.120 --> 20:04.485
FARAH: A corporation
hell-bent on making sure

20:04.560 --> 20:06.324
you don't complete your mission.

20:07.320 --> 20:08.651
MALINA: A corporation?

20:09.200 --> 20:10.361
How did they find us?

20:10.440 --> 20:12.169
I don't know, but I think

20:12.240 --> 20:14.891
those glasses he was wearing
can see our powers.

20:15.280 --> 20:16.441
(SIGHS) Malina...

20:18.120 --> 20:20.282
You don't have to
save the world alone,

20:21.120 --> 20:23.043
but if those men catch us...

20:26.560 --> 20:27.686
Come on.

20:28.240 --> 20:30.561
(THROUGH SPEAKERS) <i>All
right, so the trick here.</i>

20:30.640 --> 20:32.688
(LAUGHS)

20:33.840 --> 20:35.365
<i>The trick here is that
you don't want to use</i>

20:35.440 --> 20:36.930
<i>too much glue, all right, buddy?</i>

20:37.000 --> 20:39.401
<i>Now, we're just gonna use a
little dab around the edges</i>

20:39.480 --> 20:41.767
<i>and on the bottom, just like so.</i>

20:41.840 --> 20:44.127
<i>Then you just...</i>

20:44.200 --> 20:45.690
JOANNE: (GASPS)
(WHISPERS) <i>Exciting moment.</i>

20:45.760 --> 20:47.683
<i>Set it in.</i>
Voila, <i>nice and easy.</i>

20:47.760 --> 20:49.888
(SNIFFLES)
<i>Okay? Got it?</i>

20:50.000 --> 20:51.206
<i>Yeah.
I think he's got it, babe.</i>

20:51.280 --> 20:52.725
<i>- He's got it.</i>
JOANNE: <i>Yay.</i>

20:53.160 --> 20:55.128
<i>All right, Captain, you want
to see if she's seaworthy?</i>

20:55.360 --> 20:57.249
<i>Yeah. One, two,
three, let her rip.</i>

20:57.880 --> 21:00.565
<i>Yeah! Come on, buddy.</i>

21:01.360 --> 21:02.486
<i>We built that.</i>

21:03.000 --> 21:04.047
<i>Yeah. We did that.</i>

21:08.600 --> 21:10.648
(CELLPHONE KEYPAD BEEPING)

21:12.120 --> 21:14.202
(RING TONE)

21:18.280 --> 21:19.281
(LINE CLICKS)

21:19.360 --> 21:22.364
(SOBS) Hey, Marcy, it's Luke.

21:22.440 --> 21:24.761
Um... (SNIFFLES)

21:24.840 --> 21:27.366
I need to see Don right away.

21:28.000 --> 21:29.968
(RING TONE)

21:30.720 --> 21:32.370
Damn it.
(CELLPHONE BEEPS)

21:32.760 --> 21:34.569
Is anyone coming to meet us?

21:36.640 --> 21:39.120
Run. <i>Chalo. Chalo!</i>

21:40.880 --> 21:42.564
(PANTING)

21:44.720 --> 21:46.245
We can't keep running.

21:49.760 --> 21:50.886
I can stop them.

22:01.680 --> 22:02.727
It's not working!

22:05.040 --> 22:06.530
I can't use my powers.

22:07.200 --> 22:08.361
Get to the back.

22:08.680 --> 22:09.761
Get to the back!

22:10.480 --> 22:11.606
(SHOUTS)

22:12.480 --> 22:13.766
Oh, my God, no.

22:15.400 --> 22:16.481
(GRUNTS)

22:17.440 --> 22:19.602
Oh! I can't.
Go, just go.

22:19.680 --> 22:21.170
I'm not leaving you.

22:21.240 --> 22:24.130
When the time comes,
you will know what to do.

22:24.200 --> 22:26.123
The answers you need
are in this envelope.

22:27.600 --> 22:29.011
Run. Run!

22:30.640 --> 22:32.130
(GROANS)

22:42.640 --> 22:44.722
(ENGINE RUMBLING)
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

23:03.720 --> 23:04.801
(GRUNTING)

23:18.920 --> 23:21.685
Tommy!
Oh, my gosh!

23:22.520 --> 23:23.931
You're okay.

23:24.520 --> 23:26.170
It's all gonna be okay.

23:26.320 --> 23:29.324
No, it's not gonna be okay.
It's never going to be okay.

23:29.400 --> 23:31.448
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

23:31.680 --> 23:33.011
It really doesn't matter.

23:33.440 --> 23:34.930
That's not the problem.

23:35.880 --> 23:37.041
What is it?

23:38.880 --> 23:40.848
- She's not my mom.
- What?

23:41.160 --> 23:43.003
My mom, she's not my mom!

23:44.040 --> 23:46.168
Our blood types don't match,
and I didn't even know,

23:46.240 --> 23:47.765
and I've got
all these different names,

23:47.840 --> 23:49.649
and I don't even know
if mine is real.

23:51.560 --> 23:53.164
Lots of people are adopted.

23:54.880 --> 23:57.247
I mean, it's not okay
that your mom didn't tell you.

23:59.040 --> 24:01.361
Being adopted
isn't any big deal.

24:01.960 --> 24:04.327
People are test-tube babies
and surrogate babies.

24:04.400 --> 24:05.526
She lied to me...

24:07.240 --> 24:08.890
About everything.

24:10.040 --> 24:12.042
I don't even know who I am.

24:19.400 --> 24:20.811
You've got to talk to her,

24:22.120 --> 24:23.804
give her a chance to explain.

24:28.880 --> 24:30.609
(BOTH PANTING)

24:33.720 --> 24:35.609
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

24:56.640 --> 24:57.721
(ENGINE STARTS)

25:00.400 --> 25:01.526
(GASPS)

25:02.560 --> 25:03.607
(TIRES SCREECHING)

25:03.760 --> 25:05.489
(CONTINUE CONVERSING
IN JAPANESE)

25:13.440 --> 25:15.283
(COMPUTER PROCESSING)

25:15.920 --> 25:17.604
(PINGING)

25:17.760 --> 25:19.330
(CHUCKLES)

25:19.480 --> 25:21.528
(INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER)

25:29.560 --> 25:30.641
(GROANS)

25:34.360 --> 25:35.566
(ENGINE STARTS)

25:37.960 --> 25:39.086
(TIRES SCREECHING)

25:43.280 --> 25:44.691
What the hell's going on?

25:45.040 --> 25:46.530
We got a problem down here.

25:47.120 --> 25:49.122
(BANGING)
(GRUNTS)

25:50.520 --> 25:51.931
(TIRES SCREECH)

25:53.960 --> 25:55.007
(GROANS)

25:55.080 --> 25:56.206
(GRUNTS)

26:02.320 --> 26:03.321
(GROANS)

26:13.640 --> 26:14.846
(BOTH GRUNTING)

26:16.880 --> 26:18.848
(CHOKING)

26:19.680 --> 26:20.966
What the hell are
you doing here?

26:21.040 --> 26:22.644
You took my friends.

26:23.080 --> 26:27.722
Loan leave you here and let
your men tear you apart, or...

26:30.040 --> 26:31.690
You take me to where they are.

26:33.000 --> 26:34.445
- Okay, okay.
- Yeah.

26:35.800 --> 26:36.847
Really?

26:36.960 --> 26:38.121
(GROANS)

26:41.200 --> 26:42.326
Really.

26:45.840 --> 26:46.921
(ENGINE STARTS)

26:47.040 --> 26:49.042
(ENGINE ROARING)
(TIRES SCREECHING)

26:53.240 --> 26:55.322
(GUNSHOTS)

26:57.520 --> 26:59.045
(DOOR SECURITY DEVICE BEEPS)

27:03.280 --> 27:04.805
Sorry I interrupted your day.

27:06.560 --> 27:09.166
It seems that you are
always sorry for something.

27:10.360 --> 27:12.044
Tell me why you went
behind my back.

27:12.880 --> 27:14.450
I just wanted answers.

27:15.520 --> 27:16.931
But you didn't trust me
to give them to you?

27:17.480 --> 27:18.970
It's not about trust.

27:19.280 --> 27:20.964
It's just, whenever
I ask you a question,

27:21.040 --> 27:23.805
all I wind up with
is more questions.

27:24.280 --> 27:27.250
This whole thing is about
your friend, Francis?

27:27.320 --> 27:29.129
We were more than friends,

27:29.240 --> 27:31.527
and I asked you
if you killed him.

27:31.600 --> 27:33.125
Which was utterly ridiculous.

27:33.200 --> 27:36.170
Maybe, but you didn't tell
me what you did do with him.

27:36.280 --> 27:37.964
You didn't tell me he was
locked in the basement,

27:38.520 --> 27:41.410
wired up in some kind of pod,
along with all those other Evos.

27:41.480 --> 27:43.881
Francis knew exactly
what he was getting into

27:43.960 --> 27:45.724
when he came to work
for Renautas.

27:45.840 --> 27:47.330
He believes in what we're doing.

27:47.840 --> 27:49.251
What exactly is that, Mother?

27:50.560 --> 27:52.847
Saving the future
that we've squandered,

27:52.920 --> 27:54.888
and that requires sacrifice.

27:56.600 --> 27:57.601
Molly Walker...

27:58.040 --> 27:59.610
Did she understand
about sacrifice, too?

27:59.680 --> 28:01.045
Is that why she blew
her brains out?

28:01.120 --> 28:02.645
I cannot talk to you
when you are like this.

28:02.720 --> 28:04.484
You are being
delusional and paranoid.

28:04.680 --> 28:05.841
(CHUCKLES)

28:07.280 --> 28:08.884
It's happening again, isn't it?

28:13.760 --> 28:14.921
You're using.

28:15.400 --> 28:16.481
I'm not using.

28:16.760 --> 28:18.330
Don't try to blame this on me.

28:19.280 --> 28:20.805
We have been
down this road, Taylor.

28:20.880 --> 28:23.451
- I know the signs.
- Mom, I'm not using!

28:24.000 --> 28:25.729
That's exactly
what a junkie would say.

28:25.800 --> 28:27.086
I'm sorry,
but I don't believe you.

28:27.600 --> 28:28.681
NOAH: I do.

28:30.920 --> 28:32.365
Long time, Erica.

28:39.320 --> 28:40.845
So dramatic, Noah.

28:41.440 --> 28:42.601
You could have just knocked.

28:44.400 --> 28:45.561
And you...

28:46.360 --> 28:47.646
You broke my heart.

28:48.480 --> 28:50.562
I'm not so sure
you have one anymore.

28:55.560 --> 28:56.800
Where's my sister?

28:56.920 --> 28:58.922
I have no idea
what you're talking about.

28:59.040 --> 29:01.122
- "I have no idea what you're
talking about." - Okay, all right.

29:02.480 --> 29:04.130
Why don't you two
give me a minute with her?

29:07.800 --> 29:09.325
Come on, Erica,
let's take a walk.

29:14.000 --> 29:15.729
ERICA: It's hard to believe

29:15.800 --> 29:18.087
it's only been a year
since we've worked together.

29:18.480 --> 29:20.687
When Renautas took
over Primatech,

29:21.040 --> 29:23.884
I considered you
one of my greatest assets.

29:24.960 --> 29:26.962
Who could have imagined
this scenario?

29:35.160 --> 29:37.208
What is on your mind, Noah?

29:40.520 --> 29:42.124
Did you kill my daughter?

29:44.880 --> 29:47.884
I had nothing to do
with Claire's death.

29:48.320 --> 29:49.685
And Hiro Nakamura?

29:50.360 --> 29:53.284
He died at the Summit
with all the rest.

29:55.760 --> 29:57.683
You can blame
Mohinder Suresh for that.

29:58.560 --> 30:00.210
And Molly Walker.

30:00.840 --> 30:02.808
You gonna stand there and claim

30:02.880 --> 30:05.167
that her blood is
not on your hands?

30:05.720 --> 30:08.246
Molly Walker was part of
something larger than herself.

30:09.080 --> 30:11.401
She just couldn't get past
her own selfishness and fear.

30:14.600 --> 30:17.490
What is so big and so important

30:18.480 --> 30:20.084
that it is worth Molly's life

30:20.160 --> 30:21.764
and the lives
of all those other people

30:21.880 --> 30:23.723
you have locked up
in that basement?

30:24.560 --> 30:26.130
Us, Noah.

30:27.760 --> 30:28.807
This planet.

30:30.760 --> 30:32.444
There is no cost too high.

30:32.800 --> 30:33.881
Including murder?

30:33.960 --> 30:35.689
(CHUCKLES) That's
what's wrong with you.

30:36.120 --> 30:39.124
You grew soft,
and like most of humanity,

30:39.200 --> 30:42.409
you are not willing to do
what's necessary, but I am.

30:44.400 --> 30:46.050
I am giving us a future.

30:47.440 --> 30:48.521
Somebody has to.

30:48.600 --> 30:51.080
NOAH: How exactly
does this work,

30:51.200 --> 30:53.806
this big sacrifice of yours?

30:56.160 --> 30:58.401
ERICA: Why should I tell you?

30:59.240 --> 31:01.811
You're the one
who chose to forget,

31:02.960 --> 31:06.885
who chose to wipe his own
memory, all to protect...

31:06.960 --> 31:08.200
What... What?

31:10.440 --> 31:11.646
To protect what?

31:12.200 --> 31:13.486
(CHUCKLES)

31:13.680 --> 31:15.808
You mean "who," don't you?

31:16.400 --> 31:18.607
I'm tired of this game.
I want answers!

31:18.680 --> 31:21.331
You can put the gun down now.

31:26.480 --> 31:27.891
Thank you, Harris.

31:27.960 --> 31:29.371
Your errand was
certainly timely.

31:40.080 --> 31:41.525
His friends are in the kitchen.

31:41.680 --> 31:43.648
Not a problem.
I brought company.

31:43.960 --> 31:45.166
(DOORBELL RINGS)

31:48.400 --> 31:50.402
(PANTING) Luke. Marcy told
me it was an emergency.

31:50.480 --> 31:51.686
I came as soon as I could.

31:52.120 --> 31:53.201
Uh, come in.

31:53.320 --> 31:54.731
Can I get you a drink
or something?

31:55.000 --> 31:56.923
No, no. No, I'm...
I'm fine.

31:57.720 --> 32:00.121
Why am I here, Luke?
I got patients waiting.

32:01.360 --> 32:04.170
How much will you pay me for
my share of the practice, Don?

32:04.320 --> 32:05.685
Don't think about it.
Just tell me.

32:05.880 --> 32:07.370
Look, I'm gonna head back
to the office, all right?

32:07.440 --> 32:08.441
We can talk about this
in the morning.

32:08.520 --> 32:09.567
Do you want the practice?

32:11.160 --> 32:12.366
If you asked me a year ago...

32:12.440 --> 32:14.090
Do you want the practice, Don?

32:15.320 --> 32:16.367
Yeah.

32:16.600 --> 32:18.841
That's great.
(INHALES DEEPLY)

32:19.200 --> 32:21.202
Just, uh...
Just write me a check.

32:22.880 --> 32:24.405
You making a change

32:25.240 --> 32:26.526
or just retiring?

32:36.280 --> 32:37.520
Atoning.

32:41.720 --> 32:44.485
Richard called.
He says it's important.

32:44.840 --> 32:46.968
Please. Everything
is important to Richard,

32:47.040 --> 32:48.644
how many loads
we can transfer per day,

32:48.840 --> 32:50.683
how he takes his coffee.

32:52.840 --> 32:54.604
Fine.
What is it this time?

32:55.040 --> 32:56.963
I don't know. We'll go see
him when we're done here.

32:57.040 --> 32:58.565
You're not getting
away with this.

32:58.640 --> 32:59.766
Everybody's gonna know...

32:59.840 --> 33:01.080
(GRUNTS)
(GROANING)

33:02.080 --> 33:03.650
What would you like
to do with them?

33:04.040 --> 33:05.246
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

33:13.440 --> 33:15.044
(GRUNTS)
(GRUNTS)

33:18.600 --> 33:19.681
(GRUNTING)

33:22.080 --> 33:24.242
Give me the sword, now.

33:29.200 --> 33:30.247
(GRUNTS)

33:30.360 --> 33:31.407
(GROANS)

33:32.520 --> 33:34.090
- You got this?
- Yeah.

33:39.440 --> 33:41.442
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

33:42.280 --> 33:43.406
(DOOR SLIDES CLOSE)

33:52.960 --> 33:54.803
(SPEAKING JAPANESE)

34:01.760 --> 34:02.807
(CHUCKLES)

34:08.639 --> 34:09.721
<i>Arigato.</i>

34:23.440 --> 34:24.487
Yes!

34:27.880 --> 34:29.723
(EKG BEEPING)

34:30.159 --> 34:31.161
Tommy.

34:32.000 --> 34:33.489
(SIGHS) Thank God
you're all right.

34:34.600 --> 34:36.648
What did they do to you?
What did you tell them?

34:36.760 --> 34:38.125
What did I tell them?

34:38.679 --> 34:40.681
I don't know, Mom.
What could I tell them?

34:40.840 --> 34:43.047
Not the truth, 'cause
I don't know the truth, do I?

34:46.679 --> 34:47.841
You lied to me.

34:50.480 --> 34:52.130
You've always lied to me.

34:52.920 --> 34:54.364
- Nathan...
- Nathan?

34:54.520 --> 34:56.966
Is that even my name, who I am?

34:58.120 --> 35:00.566
- Where did I come from?
- You are my son.

35:01.520 --> 35:03.170
No matter what name
we are using,

35:03.240 --> 35:05.561
you have always been my son.

35:07.240 --> 35:09.208
I wanted to tell
you. I did...

35:10.080 --> 35:12.208
But there just never
seemed to be a good time.

35:14.480 --> 35:16.209
But I will tell you everything.

35:18.280 --> 35:19.850
CASPAR: Everything, Anne?

35:21.000 --> 35:22.764
You really ready
to tell him everything?

35:22.960 --> 35:24.371
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

35:34.560 --> 35:35.721
NOAH: I lost them.

35:36.080 --> 35:38.401
There must be a secret exit,
like a tunnel or something.

35:38.560 --> 35:40.961
Where is my sister,
Phoebe Frady?

35:41.320 --> 35:43.049
Oh, easy, easy.
That's enough.

35:43.160 --> 35:45.128
Are you kidding me?
Are you kidding me, man?

35:45.240 --> 35:46.571
We got him right where we want him.
(CHUCKLES)

35:46.640 --> 35:48.529
We could beat the answers
out of him if we want to,

35:48.600 --> 35:50.090
but now you want to
wuss out on me?

35:50.320 --> 35:51.970
(GUN COCKS)
Where is my sister?

35:52.040 --> 35:53.644
Quentin, that's enough.

35:55.760 --> 35:57.444
You know him
and you didn't tell me?

35:57.800 --> 35:59.564
Of course your mother knows me.

35:59.920 --> 36:01.160
I've been around for a while.

36:01.240 --> 36:03.561
- How long?
- Over a year now.

36:03.680 --> 36:04.920
A Year?

36:06.720 --> 36:08.882
(STAMMERS) Wait.
Are you my dad?

36:09.560 --> 36:11.801
No. He's not your dad.

36:12.600 --> 36:15.046
Then why have you been following me for...
For a year?

36:15.120 --> 36:16.451
(SIGHS)

36:17.120 --> 36:19.088
Because you're
that important, Tommy,

36:19.560 --> 36:21.085
very important.

36:21.320 --> 36:22.651
I couldn't tell you.

36:23.640 --> 36:26.246
I had to take you away
before you found out,

36:26.360 --> 36:29.170
'cause I was afraid that
when you found out, you...

36:30.400 --> 36:32.050
You would try to save your dad.

36:34.640 --> 36:36.642
- I couldn't lose you both.
(SIGHS)

36:37.120 --> 36:38.610
You shouldn't have run.

36:39.000 --> 36:40.923
Then this wouldn't
have happened.

36:41.960 --> 36:43.724
What do you want with me?

36:43.800 --> 36:45.882
Why am I so important?

36:46.440 --> 36:48.363
You have a destiny.

36:49.280 --> 36:52.489
Humanity has one last
hope for survival,

36:53.440 --> 36:55.681
and part of it rests
on your shoulders.

36:57.280 --> 36:59.089
What does that even mean?

37:01.320 --> 37:02.481
(SIGHS)

37:04.440 --> 37:06.807
You're going to help
save the world.

37:10.720 --> 37:11.801
No.

37:13.360 --> 37:14.441
I'm not.

37:20.160 --> 37:22.162
(SOBBING)

37:25.480 --> 37:27.244
(PANTING)

38:18.480 --> 38:20.164
(SMOKE ALARM BEEPING)

38:28.200 --> 38:30.248
(SMOKE ALARM BLARING)

39:06.960 --> 39:08.405
(ENGINE WHIRRING)

39:40.440 --> 39:43.569
Erica, thank God.
Are you okay?

39:43.840 --> 39:46.446
ERICA: Of course.
Just a minor inconvenience.

39:47.160 --> 39:50.403
I'm afraid Mr. Harris here
underestimated the situation,

39:51.960 --> 39:53.689
but I'm sure
he won't do it again.

39:56.480 --> 39:58.403
Right. Well,
the reason I called,

39:58.480 --> 40:01.006
things are happening much more
quickly than we anticipated.

40:01.360 --> 40:02.486
How quickly?

40:02.800 --> 40:03.881
Less than a week.

40:05.480 --> 40:07.403
Have you run the simulation?

40:07.640 --> 40:09.165
Yes, that's what
I needed you to see.

40:13.880 --> 40:15.689
With the magnetic
poles reversing,

40:15.760 --> 40:17.285
we are going to be defenseless

40:17.360 --> 40:19.408
against solar radiation.

40:19.520 --> 40:21.488
A coronal mass ejection
unlike anything

40:21.560 --> 40:24.131
the world has ever seen
is headed our way.

40:24.840 --> 40:26.842
We're talking total devastation,

40:27.640 --> 40:30.041
96% of all species on Earth

40:30.120 --> 40:32.566
wiped out in a matter of days.

40:34.680 --> 40:36.444
It's worse
than we ever expected.

40:38.080 --> 40:40.048
What did you expect, Richard?

40:42.480 --> 40:44.164
Starting over is never pretty.

40:44.960 --> 40:47.008
(SCORCHING)

40:54.200 --> 40:55.281
(MUSIC PLAYING)

40:58.500 --> 41:06.500
